cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with improving the resolution of widefield fluorescent microscopy. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it uses deep neural networks for blind deconvolution. Additionally, it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it uses neural networks, and the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it deals with modeling the point spread function.
